  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use this lesson when you want to understand computation at its most fundamental level — before types, before programming languages, before machines. The lambda calculus is a formal system where every computation is expressed using only three constructs: variables, function definitions, and function application.\nNo prior knowledge of logic, type theory, or programming is assumed. If you have written functions in any programming language, the intuitions will be familiar.\n",
